  "prompt": "What is the average CPF cash balance for a member at the age of 55 in Singapore?",
  "response": "The average CPF (Central Provident Fund) cash balance for a member at the age of 55 in Singapore can vary from year to year and depends on various factors such as individual contributions, withdrawals, and investment choices. However, according to recent data, the average CPF savings for a member at age 55 is around SGD 130,000 to SGD 150,000.\n\nPlease note that this is an average figure, and actual balances can differ significantly from one individual to another. For the most current and accurate information, it's best to refer to the latest reports and statistics provided by the CPF Board.",
